  "about": {
    "title": "About DFR Browser 2",
    "content": "This demonstration shows the WoS-Core-corpus-22-topic model from Alan Liu's <a href=\"https:\/\/alanyliu.org\/citation\/kit-for-exploring-articles-on-ai-published-in-2024\" target=\"_blank\">\"Kit for Exploring Articles on AI Published in 2024.\"<\/a> It is based on a collection of 227 “highly cited” English-language journal articles published in in the Web of Science Core Collection index for 2024 that mention “artificial intelligence” or “AI” in their titles. (For more information and context, <a href=\"https:\/\/alanyliu.org\/citation\/kit-for-exploring-articles-on-ai-published-in-2024\" target=\"_blank\">go to the kit<\/a>.\n\<h2 style=\"margin-bottom: -.5em;\">About DFR Browser 2<\/h2>\n\n<a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/scottkleinman\/dfr-browser2\" target=\"_blank\">DFR Browser 2<\/a> is an interactive web application developed by <a href=\"https:\/\/scottkleinman.com\" target=\"_blank\">Scott Kleinman<\/a> for exploring topic models and document collections. It is based on the original <a href=\"https:\/\/agoldst.github.io\/dfr-browser\/\" target=\"_blank\">DFR Browser<\/a> created by Andrew Goldstone. However, it has been re-engineered from the ground up with new features. These include:\n\n**Features:**\n\n- Updated <a href=\"https:\/\/getbootstrap.com\/\" target=\"_blank\">Bootstrap<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/d3js.org\/\" target=\"_blank\">D3<\/a> libraries\n- Page routing with <a href=\"https:\/\/visionmedia.github.io\/page.js\/\" target=\"_blank\">page.js<\/a>\n- Multilingual sorting capabilities\n- Embargo-controlled document access\n- Optional upload form for MALLET data and metadata\n- Handling of bibliography using CSL-JSON fields\n- Overall, a fresh look\n\n**How to Use DFR Browser 2 to Explore a Topic Model:**\nFor a basic description of the interface, see <a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/scottkleinman\/dfr-browser2?tab=readme-ov-file#application-views\" target=\"_blank\">\"Application Views\"<\/a>. For more detailed explanations of the original, similar dfr-browser and how to read a topic model, see the WE1S Project's <a href=\"https:\/\/live-we1s-ucsb-edu-v01.pantheonsite.io\/research\/we1s-tools-and-software\/topic-model-observatory\/tmo-guide\/tmo-guide-dfr-browser\" target=\"_blank\">\"Topic Model Observatory Guide: Dfr-browser\"<\/a> and the <em>Signs<\/em> journal's \"An Interactive Topic Model of <em>Signs<\/em>\": <a href=\"https:\/\/signsat40.signsjournal.org\/topic-model\" target=\"_blank\">\"Getting Started\"<\/a>."
  }
